trend_summary: Initial image shows mainly forest and scattered villages. Each subsequent year exhibits progressive infill: ribbon housing spreads along the main north–south highway, planned estates multiply in the west, and light-industrial roofs appear near the reservoir. Forest and farmland steadily contract, converting the landscape from rural to clearly suburban by the last frame.
notable_changes: Housing estates spread west of the central highway, filling former forest gaps.
Industrial/commercial rooftops emerge near the reservoir’s southern shore.
Progressive deforestation and farmland loss across northwest and southeast zones.
Main highway widened and supplemented by new feeder and ring roads.
Reservoir shoreline modified with visible reclamation and edge stabilization.
